<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 4:51AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Beaver
County through 530 AM CDT...
At 451 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boyd, or 16 miles southwest of Beaver, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Turpin, Elmwood, Floris, Bryans Corner, Balko, and Boyd.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
